Is anyone out there using the SuppDists package on Ubuntu for multi-core 
processing?

I've been using for nearly a year without problem -- with many thanks to 
Mike Rutter for his earlier help!

Recently have been having problems with spawned processes not closing 
upon completion of procedure that calls them (most often the LMER 
package) ... I'll see that RAM used by the procedure is still in use 
after the procedure is completed so I then go through the process list 
to kill the spawned processes manually.

SuppDist was originally installed on previous version of Ubuntu (64 bit) 
and in previous version of R (64 bit).  I run updates regularly, through 
apt-get updates and within R update.packages and it seems it may have 
been with the upgrade to R 2.13 that it stopped working.

