Alireza,

If you installed from source, go back to the source directory and run 
'sudo make uninstall'.  Then I would use a GUI interface Synaptic to 
make sure that all R related packages are removed.  Check to make sure 
typing 'R' returns nothing.

Then I would use these instructions to install the latest version of R:

http://cran.r-project.org/bin/linux/ubuntu/

